# CURSOR / ANTIGRAVITY RULES
# Save as .cursorrules in every project root
# Cursor and Antigravity read this automatically — never re-explain your stack

---

## WHO I AM
Solo developer, 14 years old. Building and monetizing AI web tools for a global audience.
Goal: ship one tool per week. Each tool makes $500–$2000/month passively.

## MY STACK — NEVER DEVIATE
- **Frontend:** Single `index.html` — HTML + CSS + JS in one file. No React. No Vue. No separate files.
- **Backend:** Vercel serverless functions in `api/` folder (`api/generate.js`, `api/support.js`)
- **AI:** Groq API — `https://api.groq.com/openai/v1/chat/completions`, model `llama-3.3-70b-versatile`
- **API keys:** MY keys stored in Vercel env vars (`GROQ_KEY_1` to `GROQ_KEY_5`). Never exposed to frontend. Frontend calls `/api/generate` only.
- **Key rotation:** Serverless functions rotate through keys, skip on 429
- **Auth:** Email + password via localStorage. No Firebase. No Supabase. No server auth.
- **Payments:** Payhip one-time products. No Stripe. No Razorpay.
- **Hosting:** Vercel — static `index.html` + serverless `api/`
- **Fonts:** Clash Display + Cabinet Grotesk + Space Mono from Google Fonts. ALWAYS.
- **Design:** Dark theme, gold/green accents, custom cursor, particle canvas, cinematic intro

## MONETIZATION MODEL — ALWAYS THIS
- Free: [N] lifetime tries (default 3)
- Daily cap: 10 generations/day even for paid users (protects my Groq bill)
- Paid: $4.99 one-time via Payhip → access code → `unlimited: true` in localStorage
- Support chat: always free, no daily cap, always works

## DAILY CAP — ALWAYS INCLUDE THIS
```js
// Check and reset daily count
function checkDailyLimit(userData) {
  const today = new Date().toDateString();
  if (userData.dailyDate !== today) {
    userData.dailyCount = 0;
    userData.dailyDate = today;
  }
  return userData.dailyCount >= 10;
}
// Increment after successful generation
function incrementDaily(email) {
  const users = getUsers();
  const today = new Date().toDateString();
  if (users[email].dailyDate !== today) {
    users[email].dailyCount = 0;
    users[email].dailyDate = today;
  }
  users[email].dailyCount = (users[email].dailyCount || 0) + 1;
  saveUsers(users);
}
```

## CRITICAL CODE RULES — NEVER BREAK THESE
1. Every HTML `id` appears EXACTLY ONCE — duplicates crash the page
2. Every `let`/`const` variable declared EXACTLY ONCE — redeclaration = JS crash
3. `#site-wrapper` starts with `filter:blur(0)` in CSS — JS adds `.blurred` on load, removes on intro exit. NEVER set blur in CSS default or page stays black forever.
4. Comment every meaningful block
5. Mentally verify ALL flows before writing:
   - New user: signup → free tries → daily cap → paywall → pay → unlimited (daily cap still applies)
   - Returning user: login → daily cap check → generate
   - Support chat: always works, no cap, no paywall
6. Mobile responsive at 768px — test mentally
7. Never output partial files — always the complete file
8. Never ask obvious questions — infer from context

## DESIGN RULES — ALWAYS
1. Background: `#050508` near-black
2. Accents: `--gold: #e8c97a`, `--green: #4fffb0` as CSS variables
3. Custom cursor: gold dot + lagging ring (disable on mobile)
4. Canvas background: 90 particles, constellation lines, mouse repulsion
5. Cinematic intro: overlay → logo → loading bar 0→100% → exit at 3.7s
6. Scroll reveals: `translateY(60px)` → 0 via IntersectionObserver
7. 3D tilt on cards via mousemove
8. Toast notifications for every user action
9. NEVER use Inter, Roboto, Arial, system-ui, or purple-on-white
10. Every tool must look like a $50/month SaaS, not a student project

## WHAT I WANT FROM YOU
- Given a tool idea → build entire production `index.html` + `api/generate.js` + `api/support.js` in one shot
- Given a bug → fix only that, touch nothing else
- Given a feature request → add cleanly, no regressions
- Never suggest a framework, backend service, or tool outside my stack
- Never output incomplete files